HEADWORD: Centrality
<hw>Cen*tral"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Centralities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The state of being
central; tendency towards a center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Meantime there is a great <qex>centrality</qex>, a centripetence
equal to the centrifugence.</q> <rj><qau>R. W. Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centralization</ent>⟦br⟧
